'''Adrien Thibault Marie Rabiot''' ({{IPA|fr|adʁijɛ̃ tibo maʁi ʁabjo}}; born 3 April 1995) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{Italian football updater|Milan}} club [[AC Milan]] and the [[France national football team|France national team]].

Rabiot spent most of his early career with [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]], making his debut with the first team in 2012 and winning eighteen major honours, including five [[Ligue 1]] titles and a [[Treble (association football)|domestic treble]] in the [[2015–16 Paris Saint-Germain F.C. season|2015–16]] and [[2017–18 Paris Saint-Germain F.C. season|2017–18]] seasons. In 2019, Rabiot signed for [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] on a free transfer, winning the [[2019–20 Serie A|Serie A title]] during his first season with the club and the [[Coppa Italia]] in his second and fifth. After a season at [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]], he signed for AC Milan in 2025.

Rabiot was [[Cap (sport)|capped]] 53 times for [[France national youth football team|France at youth level]], and made his debut for the senior team in 2016. He took part in [[UEFA Euro 2020]], the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] (reaching the [[2022 FIFA World Cup final|final]]), and [[UEFA Euro 2024|Euro 2024]].

==Club career==
===Paris Saint-Germain===
[[File:Chelsea 1 PSG 2 (25672641705) - Adrien Rabiot (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|upright|Rabiot playing for [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] in 2016]]

Rabiot was born in [[Saint-Maurice, Val-de-Marne|Saint-Maurice]], Val-de-Marne.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Adrien Rabiot {{!}} Actor |url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm11789953/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=IMDb |language=en-US}}</ref> He played youth football for several teams, including two spells at [[US Créteil-Lusitanos|Créteil]] and a few months at [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Folgoas |first=Ronan |date=2016-04-03 |title=PSG : quand Rabiot jouait pour Manchester City |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/psg/rabiot-l-histoire-du-citizen-kid-04-04-2016-5684597.php |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=leparisien.fr |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2012-07-09 |title=Adrien Rabiot : « Quelque chose de grand » |trans-title=Adrien Rabiot: "Something great" |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/psg/adrien-rabiot-quelque-chose-de-grand-09-07-2012-2083094.php |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=leparisien.fr |language=fr-FR}}</ref> On 2 July 2012, after excelling at the [[Camp des Loges]], he signed his first professional contract agreeing to a three-year deal with [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.psg.fr/fr/News/003001/Article/58461/First-pro-contract-for-Rabiot |title=Premier contrat professionnel pour Adrien Rabiot|trans-title=First professional contract for Adrien Rabiot |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C |language=fr |date=12 July 2012|access-date=26 August 2012|archive-date=26 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181026070020/https://www.psg.fr/fr/News/003001/Article/58461/First-pro-contract-for-Rabiot|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Rabiot was promoted to the senior team by manager [[Carlo Ancelotti]] ahead of the [[2012–13 Ligue 1|2012–13 season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.le10sport.com/football/france/ligue1/psg-rabiot-la-derniere-surprise-signee-ancelotti70618 |title=Rabiot, la dernière surprise signée Ancelotti|trans-title=Rabiot, the last surprise signed Ancelotti |publisher=Le 10 Sport |language=fr |date=5 August 2012|access-date=26 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Moradi |first=Kasra |date=2024-09-10 |title=Adrien Rabiot's 'authoritarian' mum – Outbursts, Paul Pogba spat, controversies |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/adrien-rabiot-mother-veronique-controversies-33633022 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=Daily Mirror |language=en}}</ref> In the club's pre-season he started in the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]] defeat to [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=2012-08-08 |title=PSG : le fabuleux destin d'Adrien Rabiot |trans-title=PSG: The fabulous destiny of Adrien Rabiot |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/psg/le-fabuleux-destin-d-adrien-rabiot-08-08-2012-2117805.php |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=leparisien.fr |language=fr-FR}}</ref> and, on 26 August, played his first game in [[Ligue 1]], a 0–0 home draw against [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.football.fr/psg/articles-blog/adrien-rabiot-le-milieu-de-terrain-du-paris-saint-germain-a-vecu-sa-premiere-titularisation-avec-l-equipe-premiere-face-aux-girondins-de-bordeaux.-175260/ |title=Rabiot, la révélation parisienne!|trans-title=Rabiot, the Parisian revelation! |publisher=Football.fr |language=fr |date=28 August 2012|access-date=21 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304030512/http://www.football.fr/psg/articles-blog/adrien-rabiot-le-milieu-de-terrain-du-paris-saint-germain-a-vecu-sa-premiere-titularisation-avec-l-equipe-premiere-face-aux-girondins-de-bordeaux.-175260/|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Rabiot made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut on 6 November 2012, playing during injury time in a [[2012–13 UEFA Champions League|4–0 group stage home win]] over [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fr.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0203-0e80cd93c50b-94304829434b-1000--le-psg-aux-portes-de-la-qualification/ |title=Le PSG aux portes de la qualification|trans-title=PSG on the verge of qualification |publisher=UEFA |language=fr |date=6 November 2012|access-date=15 February 2014}}</ref> In January of the following year he was loaned to fellow league side [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.psg.fr/fr/Actus/003001/Article/60810/Adrien-Rabiot-prete-a-Toulouse |title=Adrien Rabiot prêté à Toulouse|trans-title=Adrien Rabiot loaned to Toulouse |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C |language=fr |date=31 January 2014|access-date=15 February 2014}}</ref> scoring his first professional goal on 9 March 2013 which was the game's only goal at [[Stade Brestois 29|Brest]], from 25 yards.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Stade Brestois-TFC (0-1) : Rabiot relance Toulouse |trans-title=Stade Brestois-TFC (0–1): Rabiot puts Toulouse back on track |url=https://www.eurosport.fr/football/ligue-1/2012-2013/stade-brestois-tfc-(0-1)-rabiot-relance-toulouse_sto3658809/story.shtml |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=www.eurosport.fr}}</ref>

Returning to PSG, Rabiot contributed with 46 matches and six goals<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/fr/news/29/ligue-1/2015/02/21/9153732/psg-rabiot-aux-anges-apr%C3%A8s-son-doubl%C3%A9 |title=PSG, Rabiot aux anges après son double|trans-title=PSG, Rabiot in heaven after brace |publisher=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |language=fr |date=21 February 2015|access-date=21 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.leparisien.fr/psg-foot-paris-saint-germain/ligue-1-paris-vainqueur-de-reims-3-2-lorgne-sur-le-triple-24-05-2015-4797055.php |title=PSG – Reims (3–2): Paris lorgne sur le triplé|trans-title=PSG – Reims (3–2): Paris eyes three-peat |newspaper=Le Parisien |language=fr |date=24 May 2015|access-date=21 October 2015}}</ref> combined as the team won back-to-back domestic leagues from [[2013–14 Ligue 1|2013]] to [[2014–15 Ligue 1|2015]], but seemed to be on the verge of leaving the club as his mother Véronique acted as his main advisor during negotiations for a better contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.maxifoot.fr/football/article-25538.htm |title=Transfert: la mère de Rabiot règle ses comptes avec le PSG et réclame un départ!|trans-title=Transfer: Rabiot's mother settles the finance with PSG and demands out! |publisher=Maxifoot |language=fr |date=18 June 2015|access-date=21 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sofoot.com/adrien-rabiot-pour-l-exemple-203373.html |title=Adrien Rabiot, pour l'exemple?|trans-title=Adrien Rabiot, as an example? |publisher=So Foot |language=fr |date=23 June 2015|access-date=21 October 2015}}</ref> He started the [[2015–16 Ligue 1|2015–16 campaign]] by getting [[Ejection (sports)|sent off]] for two yellow cards after only 29 minutes, in the opening fixture against [[Lille OSC|Lille]] (eventual away 1–0 win).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/match/lille-vs-psg/2045807/report?ICID=MP_MS_5 |title=Lille 0–1 PSG: Lucas Moura rifles 10-man Parisiens to win |publisher=Goal |date=7 August 2015|access-date=7 August 2015}}</ref>

Rabiot scored his first goal in [[UEFA|European competition]] on 25 November 2015 to open a [[2015–16 UEFA Champions League|5–0 Champions League group win]] at [[Malmö FF|Malmö]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0253-0d808b5e2125-768cc19e90e9-1000--ibrahimovic-s-happy-return-as-paris-thrash-malmo/ |title=Ibrahimović's happy return as Paris thrash Malmö |publisher=UEFA |date=25 November 2015|access-date=10 March 2016}}</ref> and repeated the feat the following 9 March in a 2–1 victory over [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] at [[Stamford Bridge (stadium)|Stamford Bridge]], putting PSG into the quarter-finals 4–2 on aggregate.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Paris Saint-Germain beat Chelsea because of Adrien Rabiot's hair |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/paris-saint-germain-beat-chelsea-because-of-adrien-rabiots-hair |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=Fox Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> Four days later, he scored in a 9–0 routing at bottom team [[Troyes AC|Troyes]] that [[2015–16 Ligue 1|sealed the league title]] with eight matches remaining.<ref>{{Cite web |title=PSG 9-0 Troyes (13 Mar, 2016) Game Analysis - ESPN (UK) |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report/_/gameId/424452 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

On 23 April 2016, Rabiot was [[Ejection (sports)|sent off]] in [[2016 Coupe de la Ligue Final|the final]] of the [[Coupe de la Ligue]],<ref name=":0">{{Cite news |date=2016-04-23 |title=Paris St-Germain beat Lille 2-1 in the Coupe de la Ligue final |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/36121198 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> a 2–1 win over Lille.<ref name=":0" /> The following two seasons combined, he scored four times from 60 appearances and conquered the national championship in [[2017–18 Ligue 1|2017–18]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2018-07-03 |title=LaLiga - Barcelona: Abidal meets with Rabiot's mother to discuss signing PSG midfielder |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/barcelona/2018/07/03/5b3b58b9e5fdea702e8b45df.html |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=Marca in English |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Rigaux |first=Romain |title=PSG : 50 M€ demandés pour Rabiot ? |trans-title=PSG: 50 M€ wanted for Rabiot? |url=https://www.maxifoot.fr/football-rss287188/psg-demandes.php |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=www.maxifoot.fr |language=fr}}</ref> In late October 2018, both Rabiot and [[Kylian Mbappé]] were dropped from the starting XI by newly appointed manager [[Thomas Tuchel]] after they arrived late to a pre-match meeting.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Kershaw |first=Tom |date=2018-10-31 |title=Neymar says Kylian Mbappe must 'respect the schedules' after Thomas Tuchel drops PSG star for lateness |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/kylian-mbappe-neymar-psg-late-training-thomas-tuchel-adrien-rabiot-barcelona-champions-league-a8608756.html |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=www.independent.co.uk |language=en-GB}}</ref> The following January, after refusing to renew his contract and failing to appear for the first team since the previous month, the former midfielder was forced to train with the reserves.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Adrien Rabiot calls on French FA to force Paris Saint-Germain to allow him to return to first-team setup |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11820/11613956/adrien-rabiot-calls-on-french-fa-to-force-paris-saint-germain-to-allow-him-to-return-to-first-team-setup |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250120033500/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11820/11613956/adrien-rabiot-calls-on-french-fa-to-force-paris-saint-germain-to-allow-him-to-return-to-first-team-setup |archive-date=20 January 2025 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=Sky Sports |language=en-GB |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 14 March 2019, Rabiot was suspended by PSG until the end of the month for going to a [[nightclub]]<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |last=Bage |first=Tom |date=2019-03-17 |title=Transfer news live: €120m man on Man United and Chelsea rumours |url=https://www.football.london/premier-league/transfer-news-live-liverpool-record-15985988 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=Football London |language=en}}</ref> after a 3–1 loss to [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in the [[2018–19 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Round of 16|Champions League round of 16]] which knocked them out of the competition,<ref name=":1" /> and for liking an [[Instagram]] post by [[Patrice Evra]] celebrating United's win.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-03-14 |title=PSG outcast Rabiot suspended over night out |url=https://www.france24.com/en/20190314-psg-outcast-rabiot-suspended-over-night-out |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=France 24 |language=en}}</ref>

===Juventus===
[[File:Матч «Динамо» - «Ювентус» 0-2. 20 октября 2020 года — 1154177 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Rabiot playing for Juventus in 2020]]

On 1 July 2019, Rabiot signed for Italian [[Serie A]] champions [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] on a free transfer.<ref name="Juventus">{{Cite web |url=http://www.juventus.com/it/news/news/2019/--bient-t--adrien-.php |title=À bientôt, Rabiot! |website=Juventus.com |language=it |date=1 July 2019|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2019-06-30 |title=Adrien Rabiot joins Juventus from Paris St-Germain on free transfer |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/48819931 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 24 August, in the team's opening match of the [[2019–20 Serie A]] season, coming on as a second-half substitute for [[Sami Khedira]] in a 1–0 away win over [[Parma Calcio 1913|Parma]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-08-24 |title=Parma 0-1 Juventus: Resumen, gol y resultado |url=https://colombia.as.com/colombia/2019/08/24/futbol/1566658159_021814.html |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=Diario AS |language=es-co}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 7 July 2020 – the opening goal in a 4–2 away loss to [[A.C. Milan|Milan]] in Serie A – with a "spectacular finish from the edge of the box – after running with the ball from his own half."<ref>{{Cite news |date=2020-07-07 |title=AC Milan 4-2 Juventus: Zlatan Ibrahimovic scores as Milan beat Serie A leaders |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53327400 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/ac-milan-vs-juventus-score-cristiano-ronaldo-scores-but-serie-a-leaders-collapse-in-second-half/live/ |title=AC Milan vs. Juventus score: Cristiano Ronaldo scores, but Serie A leaders collapse in second half |publisher=CBSSports.com |last1=Gonzalez |first1=Roger |date=7 July 2020 |access-date=8 July 2020}}</ref>

On 9 March 2021, he scored his first Champions League goal with Juventus in a 3–2 win after extra-time against [[FC Porto|Porto]] in the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League]] round of 16; however, Juventus were eliminated on away goals.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2021-03-08 |title=Juventus 3-2 Porto (4-4 agg): Sergio Oliveira's extra-time goal sees Porto advance on away goals |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56325263 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2021-03-08 |title=Juventus 3-2 Porto (4-4 agg): Sergio Oliveira's extra-time goal sees Porto advance on away goals |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56325263 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 27 June 2023, he signed a one-year contract extension with the club until 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66034421 |title=Adrien Rabiot signs one-year contract extension with Juventus |website=BBC Sport |date=27 June 2023}}</ref> On 30 December, he scored the winning goal in a 1–0 victory over [[AS Roma|Roma]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-12-30 |title=Juventus 1-0 Roma: Juventus beat Roma to narrow gap on leaders Inter |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67851068 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

He left Juventus in July 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-07-18 |title=France midfielder Adrien Rabiot has left Juventus after contract expires |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c87r3820m4jo |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Puikys |first=Laurynas |date=2024-07-04 |title=Man Utd 'Offer Three-Year Contract' to Adrien Rabiot |url=https://www.givemesport.com/manchester-united-make-three-year-offer-to-adrien-rabiot/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref>

===Marseille===
On 17 September 2024, Rabiot signed for French side [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] on a free transfer.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-17 |title=Adrien Rabiot: France midfielder joins Marseille |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c5y5r8l1gxxo |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-17 |title=Ex-PSG star Rabiot joins Marseille on free transfer |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/41301775/france-adrien-rabiot-signs-marseille-transfer |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref>

On 19 August 2025, the club announced that Rabiot, alongside teammate [[Jonathan Rowe (footballer, born 2003)|Jonathan Rowe]], had been placed on the transfer list due to "unacceptable behavior in the locker room" following Marseille's 1–0 loss away to [[Stade Rennais FC|Rennes]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Communiqué officiel - OM |url=https://www.om.fr/fr/actualites/4808/club/100564-communique-officiel |access-date=2025-08-19 |website=www.om.fr |language=fr}}</ref> Their altercation was described as an "English pub fight" by manager [[Roberto De Zerbi]], and as "extremely violent" by president [[Pablo Longoria]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-08-22 |title=De Zerbi: Rabiot, Rowe had 'English pub fight' |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/46049719/rabiot-rowe-altercation-marseille-was-english-pub-fight-roberto-de-zerbi |access-date=2025-09-05 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref>

===AC Milan===
On 1 September 2025, Rabiot returned to Serie A, joining [[AC Milan]] on a three-year deal.<ref>{{cite news |title=Adrien Rabiot, new signing of AC Milan's transfer market: the official statement |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/media/2025-09-01/official-statement-adrien-rabiot |date=1 September 2025 |access-date=1 September 2025 |publisher=AC Milan}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=AC Milan signs midfielder Adrien Rabiot from Olympique De Marseille: the official statement |url= https://sportstar.thehindu.com/football/adrien-rabiot-transfer-free-ac-milan-marseille-fee-serie-a-details-summer-window-deadline-day-news/article70002696.ece |date= 1 September 2025 |access-date=1 September 2025 |publisher=Sportstar}}</ref> 
He scored his first goal for the club in an away game against Torino on 8 December and made the score 2-1 in an eventual 2-3 comeback win.
On 15 January 2026 he scored a brace in a 1-3 away win against Como. On 19 April 2026, he scored the sole goal against [[Hellas Verona FC|Hellas Verona]] in a 0-1 win for Milan.

==International career==
[[File:Rus-Fra 2018 (3) (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|Rabiot playing for France in 2018.]]

Rabiot was a member of the [[France national under-19 football team|France U19 side]] that reached the final of the [[2013 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]] in Lithuania, losing out to [[Serbia national under-19 football team|Serbia]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/news/0257-0decebf0341c-ecee3334728d-1000--serbia-climb-on-to-under-19-honours-board/ |title=Serbia climb on to Under-19 honours board |publisher=[[UEFA]] |date=1 August 2013 |access-date=6 December 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/news/0252-0ce44aba6512-27448958cba2-1000--rabiot-rues-france-s-missed-final-chance/?iv=true |title=Rabiot rues France's missed final chance |publisher=[[UEFA]] |last=Haslam |first=Andrew |date=1 August 2013 |access-date=6 December 2020}}</ref>

On 13 August 2013, aged just 18, Rabiot made his first appearance for the [[France national under-21 football team|French under-21 team]], starting in a 0–0 [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] draw with [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany]] in [[Freiburg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.football365.fr/equipe-de-france/espoirs/amical-allemagne-france-0-0-1050475.shtml |title=Amical: Allemagne-France (0–0)|trans-title=Friendly: Germany-France (0–0) |publisher=Foot 365 |language=fr |date=13 August 2013|access-date=15 February 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302201933/http://www.football365.fr/equipe-de-france/espoirs/amical-allemagne-france-0-0-1050475.shtml|archive-date=2 March 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> He was on standby for [[France national football team|the full side]]'s [[UEFA Euro 2016]] squad,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.co.uk/france/story/2870292/ngolo-kante-in-france-squad-for-euro-2016-but-hatem-ben-arfa-and-alexandre-lacazette-out |title=N'Golo Kante in France's Euros squad; Lacazette, Gameiro, Ben Arfa miss out |publisher=ESPN FC |date=12 May 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517073506/http://www.espnfc.co.uk/france/story/2870292/ngolo-kante-in-france-squad-for-euro-2016-but-hatem-ben-arfa-and-alexandre-lacazette-out|archive-date=17 May 2016}}</ref> but did not make the final cut.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Dernière Sélection |url=http://www.fff.fr/equipes-de-france/1/france-a/derniere-selection |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160704174711/http://www.fff.fr/equipes-de-france/1/france-a/derniere-selection |archive-date=2016-07-04 |website=Fédération Française de Football}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2016-05-30 |title=Gignac aura le numéro 10 |url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/euro-2016/fil-info/gignac-aura-le-numero-10-807454 |access-date=2024-06-24 |website=Le Figaro |language=fr}}</ref>

Rabiot made his senior debut for France on 15 November 2016 against [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast]], starting and being replaced by [[Thomas Lemar]] after 78 minutes of the 0–0 friendly home draw, due to a [[hamstring]] injury.<ref>{{Cite web |title=France 0-0 Ivory Coast (Nov 15, 2016) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=467289 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.foxsportsasia.com/news/rabiot-i-think-my-goose-is-cooked/ |title=Rabiot: I think my goose is cooked |publisher=[[Fox Sports Asia]] |date=16 November 2016|access-date=27 November 2016|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161128054359/http://www.foxsportsasia.com/news/rabiot-i-think-my-goose-is-cooked/|archive-date=28 November 2016}}</ref> On 17 May 2018, he was put on the reserve list by manager [[Didier Deschamps]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] squad.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12025/11376691/alexandre-lacazette-and-anthony-martial-on-standby-for-france-world-cup-squad-and-dimitri-payet-out |title=Alexandre Lacazette and Anthony Martial on standby for France World Cup squad and Dimitri Payet out |publisher=Sky Sports |date=17 May 2018|access-date=17 May 2018}}</ref> However, he controversially refused to be put on the standby list, emailing the coach and saying he would not "be able to follow the training programme". [[French Football Federation]] president [[Noël Le Graët]] commented: "He made a bad decision. He penalises himself and sanctions himself alone."<ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-05-23 |title=Adrien Rabiot: France midfielder refuses to be on World Cup standby list |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44229676 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 18 May 2021, Rabiot was included in France's [[UEFA Euro 2020 squads#France|26-man squad]] for [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Orsini |first=Vincent |url=https://www.fff.fr/article/2859-la-liste-des-vingt-six-pour-l-uefa-euro-2020.html |title=La liste des vingt-six pour l'UEFA Euro 2020 |trans-title=The list of 26 for UEFA Euro 2020 |work=[[French Football Federation]] |date=18 May 2021 |access-date=18 May 2021 |language=fr}}</ref> He came on as an emergency [[Fullback (association football)|left-back]] in the final [[UEFA Euro 2020 Group F|group]] game against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] due to injuries to [[Lucas Hernández]] and [[Lucas Digne]], and retained a starting role as a left [[Wing-back (association football)|wing-back]] in an untested [[Formation (association football)#3–5–2|3–5–2 formation]] against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] in the [[UEFA Euro 2020 knockout phase|last 16]];<ref>{{cite news |title=Adrien Rabiot titulaire face à la Suisse, Hernandez sur le banc |trans-title=Adrien Rabiot starter against Switzerland, Hernandez on the bench |url=https://www.sofoot.com/adrien-rabiot-titulaire-face-a-la-suisse-hernandez-sur-le-banc-501485.html |access-date=29 June 2021 |work=SoFoot |date=28 June 2021 |language=French}}</ref> his side lost in a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]] after a 3–3 draw.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tactical confusion and Mbappe missing in action – what went wrong for France? |url=https://www.bt.com/sport/news/2021/june/tactical-confusion-and-mbappe-missing-in-action-what-went-wrong-for-france |access-date=29 June 2021 |publisher=[[BT Sport]] |date=29 June 2021}}</ref>

On 13 November, Rabiot scored his first international goal in an 8–0 home win over [[Kazakhstan national football team|Kazakhstan]], which allowed France to [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification|qualify]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/590232 |title=France vs. Kazakhstan - Football Match Report |work=ESPN.com |date=13 November 2021 |access-date=14 November 2021}}</ref>

On 22 November 2022, Rabiot scored France's first goal of the 2022 FIFA World Cup in a 4–1 win over [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]] in the group stage.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Howcroft |first=Jonathan |date=2022-11-22 |title=France 4-1 Australia: World Cup 2022 – as it happened |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2022/nov/22/france-vs-australia-world-cup-qatar-2022-live-score-updates-socceroos-francia-fra-v-aus-kick-off-time-national-football-team-list-squad-soccer-fifa |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=the Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

Rabiot was selected to play in [[UEFA Euro 2024]], playing in 5 matches.<ref>{{Cite web |title=The official website for European football |url=https://www.uefa.com/errors/ |access-date=2025-08-20 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref> Before the semi-final against [[Spain national football team|Spain]], Rabiot sparked controversy over his comments regarding [[Lamine Yamal]] by saying, "...to play the final of a Euro, he’ll need to show much more than he has until now."<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-07-09 |title=Rabiot tells Spain's prodigy Lamine Yamal to "do much more" in shock pre-match warning |url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/us/en/20240709/694659/rabiot-tells-spain-s-prodigy-lamine-yamal-to-do-much-more-in-shock-pre-match-warning.html |access-date=2025-08-20 |website=Mundo Deportivo USA |language=en}}</ref> Yamal scored a goal in the match, helping Spain win 2-1 against France and celebrated by yelling "Speak now!" to the camera.<ref>{{Cite web |first=Jamie |last=Braidwood |date=2024-07-10 |title=Lamine Yamal hits back at Adrien Rabiot comments as Euro 2024 wondergoal proves point |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/lamine-yamal-hits-back-adrien-214209654.html |access-date=2025-08-20 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref>

==Style of play==
{{Quote box
 |quote = He is a complete player, I have rarely seen someone so strong both physically and technically.
|source =— [[Andrea Pirlo]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Westwood |first1=James |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/i-have-rarely-seen-someone-so-physically-technically-strong/la9vsqkab74r1m6xanlr5mue4 |title='I have rarely seen someone so physically & technically strong' - Rabiot is a complete player, says Juve boss Pirlo |publisher=Goal |date=22 November 2020|access-date=10 August 2022}}</ref>
 |align = right
 |quoted = 1
 | width = 33%
}}
A tall, strong, and elegant left-footed midfielder, who combines good technique with impressive physical qualities, Rabiot was regarded as a promising player in his youth. He is known for being mobile, hard-working, quick in possession, and for his ability to make late attacking runs off the ball into the penalty box, courtesy of his intelligent movement; he is also a composed passer, who possesses good link-up play and [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]] skills in close spaces, which enables him to create chances for teammates. A modern, well-rounded, and versatile player, with good defensive skills, he is also known for being capable of playing in several different midfield positions, including in a deep, [[Deep-lying playmaker|creative holding]] role as a [[Squad number (association football)|number 6]] in front of the defence (which is not his favoured role, however), as a [[box-to-box midfielder]], on the [[Winger (association football)|right flank]], and even as an [[Playmaker#Advanced playmakers|advanced midfield playmaker]], although he usually plays as a left–sided offensive-minded central midfielder, known as the ''[[mezzala]]'' role in Italian football jargon, which is his preferred position. His Juventus manager [[Massimiliano Allegri]] has also deployed him as a left winger on occasion. Despite his talent and ability, however, he has come under criticism in the media over his behaviour off the pitch, and has also been accused in the media of lacking professionalism, as well as having a poor attitude and a difficult character, which has led him to have conflicts with several of his managers.<ref name="Juventus"/><ref name="U19"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/club/paris-saint-germain/160/blog/post/2992058/adrien-rabiot-rise-at-paris-saint-germain-recognised-by-france-call |title=Adrien Rabiot's rise at Paris Saint-Germain recognised by France call |publisher=ESPN |last=Laurens |first=Julien |date=8 November 2016 |access-date=24 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/mar/19/adrien-rabiot-psg-contract-suspension-france-football-future |title=Adrien Rabiot: the golden boy who became PSG's French football outcast |work=The Guardian |last=Aarons |first=Ed |date=19 March 2019 |access-date=24 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.football-italia.net/140210/juventus-can-tame-rabiot |title=Juventus can tame Rabiot |work=Football Italia |last=Yakimov |first=Vilizar |date=2 July 2019 |access-date=4 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/calciomercato/2019/06/22-58237076/rabiot_due_in_uno_regista_arretrato_o_mezzala_sinistra_perfetto_per_il_4-3-3_di_sarri/ |title=Rabiot, due in uno: regista arretrato o mezzala sinistra, perfetto per il 4-3-3 di Sarri |work=Tutto Sport |language=it |date=22 June 2019 |access-date=13 June 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.it/calcio/serie-a/2018-2019/talento-carattere-e-posizione-alla-scoperta-di-adrien-rabiot-l-ultimo-acquisto-della-juventus_sto7352575/story.shtml |title=Talento, carattere e posizione: alla scoperta di Adrien Rabiot, l'ultimo acquisto della Juventus |publisher=Eurosport |date=3 July 2019 |access-date=13 June 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://football-italia.net/juventus-rabiot-disappoints-again/ |title=Juventus: Rabiot disappoints again |publisher=Football Italia |last=Bettoni |first=Lorenzo |date=7 November 2021 |access-date=14 November 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/NEWS/2020/03/23/rabiot-win-back-the-ligue-1-title |title=Rabiot: 'Win back the Ligue 1 title' |publisher=Ligue 1 |access-date=11 August 2022}}</ref>

